solution:
Clearly $x^{2}+1 \geq 2 x$, for every real $x$, and therefore
$$
\begin{aligned}
& \frac{a}{a^{2}+2 b+3}+\frac{b}{b^{2}+2 c+3}+\frac{c}{c^{2}+2 a+3} \\
& \leq \frac{a}{2(a+b+1)}+\frac{b}{2(b+c+1)}+\frac{c}{2(c+a+1)}
\end{aligned}
$$

So it remains to prove that
$$
\begin{equation*}
\frac{a}{a+b+1}+\frac{b}{b+c+1}+\frac{c}{c+a+1} \leq 1 \tag{1}
\end{equation*}
$$

Inequality (1) is equivalent to
$$
\frac{b+1}{a+b+1}+\frac{c+1}{b+c+1}+\frac{a+1}{c+a+1} \geq 2
