solution:
Let $p=a+b+c, q=a b+b c+c a=1, r=a b c$.
The given inequality is equivalent to
$$
\begin{equation*}
\frac{(a+b)(b+c)+(b+c)(c+a)+(c+a)(a+b)}{(a+b)(b+c)(c+a)}-\frac{1}{a+b+c} \geq 2 \tag{1}
\end{equation*}
