$$
i.e.
$$
\frac{a}{b^{2}+1}+\frac{b}{c^{2}+1}+\frac{c}{a^{2}+1} \geq \frac{(a \sqrt{a}+b \sqrt{b}+c \sqrt{c})^{2}}{a^{2}\left(b^{2}+1\right)+b^{2}\left(c^{2}+1\right)+c^{2}\left(a^{2}+1\right)}
$$

So it suffices to show that
$$
a^{2}\left(b^{2}+1\right)+b^{2}\left(c^{2}+1\right)+c^{2}\left(a^{2}+1\right) \leq \frac{4}{3}
$$

From the obvious inequality $\left(a^{2}-b^{2}\right)^{2}+\left(b^{2}-c^{2}\right)^{2}+\left(c^{2}-a^{2}\right)^{2} \geq 0$ we deduce that
