$$

We have
$$
\frac{x}{y+z}(B+C)=\frac{a b\left(a^{3}+b^{3}\right)}{a^{2}+b^{2}}, \quad \frac{y}{z+x}(C+A)=\frac{b c\left(b^{3}+c^{3}\right)}{b^{2}+c^{2}}
$$
and
$$
\frac{z}{x+y}(A+B)=\frac{c a\left(c^{3}+a^{3}\right)}{c^{2}+a^{2}}
$$

