By $A M \leq Q M$ we have
$$
\begin{equation*}
\frac{\sqrt{1-a}+\sqrt{a}}{2} \leq \sqrt{\frac{1-a+a}{2}}=\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}, \quad \text { i.e. } \quad \frac{1}{\sqrt{1-a}+\sqrt{a}} \geq \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}} \tag{3}
\end{equation*}
$$

Using (2) and (3) we deduce
$$
