$$
i.e.
$$
8\left(y^{2}+z^{2}\right)^{3} \geq(y+z)^{6}
$$

Using $A M \geq G M$ and the previous result we get
$$
2 x^{2}\left(y^{2}+z^{2}\right)+\left(y^{2}+z^{2}\right)^{2} \geq 2 \sqrt{2 x^{2}\left(y^{2}+z^{2}\right)^{3}} \geq 2 \sqrt{\frac{2 x^{2}(y+z)^{6}}{8}}=x(y+z)^{3}
$$
so we prove (2), i.e. (1).
