\frac{a b}{a^{5}+a b+b^{5}} \leq \frac{a b}{(a+b) a^{2} b^{2}+a b}=\frac{a b c^{2}}{(a+b) a^{2} b^{2} c^{2}+a b c^{2}}=\frac{c}{a+b+c} \tag{1}
\end{equation*}
$$

Analogously
$$
\begin{equation*}
\frac{b c}{b^{5}+b c+c^{5}} \leq \frac{a}{a+b+c} \tag{2}
\end{equation*}
$$
and
$$
\begin{equation*}
\frac{c a}{c^{5}+c a+a^{5}} \leq \frac{b}{a+b+c} \tag{3}
\end{equation*}
$$

Adding (1), (2) and (3) gives us the required inequality.

Applying $A M \geq G M$ we have
$$
