Theorem 5.Theorem:
For any real numbers $a_{1}, a_{2}, \ldots, a_{n}$ and $b_{1}, b_{2}, \ldots, b_{n}$

$$
\begin{gathered}
\left(a_{1}^{2}+a_{2}^{2}+\ldots+a_{n}^{2}\right)\left(b_{1}^{2}+b_{2}^{2}+\ldots+b_{n}^{2}\right) \geq \\
\geq\left(a_{1} b_{1}+a_{2} b_{2}+\ldots+a_{n} b_{n}\right)^{2}
\end{gathered}
$$

with equality if and only if $a_{i}$ and $b_{i}$ are proportional, $i=1,2, \ldots, n$.

solution:
Without loss of generality we may assume that $a \geq b \geq c \geq d$. Then clearly $a^{2} \geq b^{2} \geq c^{2} \geq d^{2}$.

We'll use Chebishev's inequality, i.e. we have
$$
\begin{aligned}
& (a+b+c)\left(a^{2}+b^{2}+c^{2}\right) \leq 3\left(a^{3}+b^{3}+c^{3}\right) \\
& \quad \Leftrightarrow \quad \frac{a^{3}+b^{3}+c^{3}}{a+b+c} \geq \frac{a^{2}+b^{2}+c^{2}}{3}
\end{aligned}
$$

Similarly we get
$$
\begin{aligned}
& \frac{a^{3}+b^{3}+d^{3}}{a+b+d} \geq \frac{a^{2}+b^{2}+d^{2}}{3}, \quad \frac{a^{3}+c^{3}+d^{3}}{a+c+d} \geq \frac{a^{2}+c^{2}+d^{2}}{3} \\
& \frac{b^{3}+c^{3}+d^{3}}{b+c+d} \geq \frac{b^{2}+c^{2}+d^{2}}{3}
\end{aligned}
$$

After adding these inequalities we get the required inequality.

Using $A M \geq G M$ we get
$$
\frac{a^{3}}{b^{2}}+a \geq 2 \sqrt{\frac{a^{3}}{b^{2}} \cdot a}=2 \frac{a^{2}}{b}
$$

Analogously we have
$$
\frac{b^{3}}{c^{2}}+b \geq 2 \frac{b^{2}}{c} \quad \text { and } \quad \frac{c^{3}}{a^{2}}+c \geq 2 \frac{c^{2}}{a}
$$

Adding these three inequalities we obtain
$$
\begin{equation*}
\frac{a^{3}}{b^{2}}+\frac{b^{3}}{c^{2}}+\frac{c^{3}}{a^{2}}+(a+b+c) \geq 2\left(\frac{a^{2}}{b}+\frac{b^{2}}{c}+\frac{c^{2}}{a}\right) \tag{1}
\end{equation*}
$$

We have that
$$
\begin{equation*}
\frac{a^{2}}{b}+\frac{b^{2}}{c}+\frac{c^{2}}{a} \geq a+b+c \tag{2}
\end{equation*}
$$

Now using (1) and (2) we obtain
$\frac{a^{3}}{b^{2}}+\frac{b^{3}}{c^{2}}+\frac{c^{3}}{a^{2}}+(a+b+c) \geq 2\left(\frac{a^{2}}{b}+\frac{b^{2}}{c}+\frac{c^{2}}{a}\right) \geq \frac{a^{2}}{b}+\frac{b^{2}}{c}+\frac{c^{2}}{a}+(a+b+c)$,
and equality holds iff $a=b=c$.

