$$
1+x^{2}=x y+y z+z x+x^{2}=(x+y)(x+z)
$$

Analogously we obtain
$$
1+y^{2}=(y+x)(y+z) \text { and } 1+z^{2}=(z+x)(z+y)
$$

Therefore
