p q \geq 9 r, \quad \text { i.e. } \quad q \geq 9 r \tag{4}
\end{equation*}
$$

Now using (4) we deduce that $2+q \geq 2+9 r$.
So it suffices to show that $2+9 r \geq 63 r$, which is $2 \geq 54 r \Leftrightarrow r \leq \frac{1}{27}$, which clearly holds, by (3).

We have proved (2), and we are done.

