Now using the result from Problem 89 and the inequality $a+b+c \geq \sqrt{3}$ we obtain
$$
\begin{aligned}
\frac{a^{2}}{1+a}+\frac{b^{2}}{1+b}+\frac{c^{2}}{1+c} & =a+b+c-3+\frac{1}{1+a}+\frac{1}{1+b}+\frac{1}{1+c} \\
& \geq \sqrt{3}-3+\frac{3 \sqrt{3}}{\sqrt{3}+1}=\frac{\sqrt{3}}{\sqrt{3}+1}
\end{aligned}
$$

Equality occurs if and only if $a=b=c=1 / \sqrt{3}$.

